SOFIA, Sept 30 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Tuesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- The ethnic Turkish MRF plans to propose an investigation of international company specialised in financial intelligence, to check the assets and its end-owners in troubled Corporate Commercial Bank <6C9.BB>. (24 Chasa, Capital Daily, Presa, Monitor, Trud, Standart) - Bulgaria's refugee agency said it expected increased inflows of asylum seekers due to worsening situation in Iraq and Syria, due to Islamic State operations. (Capital daily, 24 Chasa)